# Testing Patterns

## Test Pyramid

- **Unit tests** (70%): Fast, isolated, test single functions/classes
- **Integration tests** (20%): Test module interactions, external services mocked
- **E2E tests** (10%): Full system tests, real dependencies

## Backend Testing

- **Mock LLMs**: Use mock LLMs for deterministic tests
- **Mock tools**: Mock external tool calls
- **Test state transitions**: Test graph nodes in isolation
- **Test edge cases**: Test error conditions, boundary cases

## Frontend Testing

- **Component testing**: Test components in isolation (React Testing Library)
- **API mocking**: Mock API responses (MSW - Mock Service Worker)
- **E2E testing**: Use Playwright or Cypress for end-to-end tests
- **Visual regression**: Use tools like Chromatic for UI tests

## Contract Testing

- **API contracts**: Test that frontend/backend contracts match
- **Schema validation**: Validate API requests/responses match schemas
- **Breaking changes**: Detect breaking changes in API contracts early

## Test Quality

- **Coverage**: Aim for 80%+ coverage (domain logic 100%)
- **Deterministic**: No flaky tests, use mocks for non-deterministic code
- **Fast**: Unit tests run in <100ms, full suite <5min
- **Isolated**: Tests don't depend on each other or external state

## LLM Testing

- **Evaluation datasets**: Create test datasets for prompts/chains
- **LLM-as-judge**: Use LLM evaluators for quality assessment
- **Snapshot testing**: For LLM outputs (with tolerance for non-determinism)
- **A/B testing**: Compare prompt/chain versions
